{
  "stem": "9168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the major trial-- Goering's trial, the major Nazi leaders-- was the International Military Tribunal trial.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as I said, when that trial ended, then the 12 subsequent trials were prosecuted by only the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the case of each of the 12 subsequent trials, the title was the United States of America versus.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the medical case, Karl Brandt et alia-- [? and there ?] meaning and others.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but I understand that they were still considered a military tribunal.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That might not have been an international.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had-- we still had some of the court reporters who worked on the major trial.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as we developed this little group of friends, then those of us who were new for the Doctors' Trial learned from them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we met in the evenings, usually in the Grand Hotel, you know, we-- they-- they would talk about what had transpired, and we learned that way.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We also learned in our office, reporting office, just through discussions about what had happened.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were developing, certainly, an awareness about how horrible this testimony was going to be.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That we really didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there are only two groups of people, I believe, who did not know what we were going to hear in Nuremberg, and they were the court reporters and the judges before the actual-- really knew what we were going to hear.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because the-- the prosecutors, the defense counsel, all the lawyers, the interpreters, the interrogators, the translators, the document examiners, they all knew what the evidence was going to be that came out.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- no, not really.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we had not worked on anything up to that point, where they had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I did not take any of the depositions.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
